707673f-a.text:
First Avenue, east side, south from East 94th Street. View 2 is limited to the American Hospital and Home for Pet Animals, located at the S. E. corner. At the rear of same is a garage on
East 94th Street.
View 1: April 14, 1940
View 2: July 13, 1930
P. L. Sperr

707674f-b.text:
First Aeenue, north from East 94th Street. Prominently shown is a generating plant at 96th - 97th Streets. This is a unit of the Consolidated Edison Company. Note in view 2 the absence of the smoke stack atop same. View 3 is limited to the N. E. corner of East 94th Street. On the right is an eastward view towards the
East River.
View 1: August 1933
George L. Balgue
Views 2,3: April 14, 1940
P. L. Sperr
